definition.value: A minimal value is smallest value of an attribute for the entities in the defined set.
A maximal value is largest value of an attribute for the entities in the defined set.
A count of the instances of a class or members in a collection.
A union is a list of all of the values of an attribute for the entities in the defined set.
An intersection is a list of only the values of an attribute for the entities in the defined set where all entities have that value.
A sequence is an ordered list of entities. Like a set, it contains members (also called elements, or terms).

label.value: gene-disease association linked with causal mutation

definition.value: A gene-variant disease association in which a mutation in the gene/protein results in the development or maintenance of the disease.
A gene disease association in which the gene is a therapeutic marker for the disease.
A gene-disease association in which the gene/protein is involved in the etiology or maintenance of the disease.

label.value: gene-disease association linked with genetic variation

definition.value: A gene-disease association in which a sequence variation (a mutation, a SNP) is associated with the disease.

label.value: gene-disease association linked with altered gene expression

definition.value: A gene-disease association in which the disease phenotype is associated with an altered expression of the gene.

label.value: gene-disease association linked with post-translational modification

definition.value: A gene-disease association in which the disease phenotype is associated with post-translational modifications in the protein product.
A process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transcription.
A process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of translation.
A process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of process involved in the creation or destruction of a molecule.
A process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of process involved in the production of a molecule.
A process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of process involved in the destruction of a molecule.
A process mediated by a protein that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of translation.
A process mediated by rna that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of translation.
The process of maintaining some the frequency, rate or extent of another process.

label.value: increased frequency of process from increased regulation

definition.value: The increase of regulation leads to a increased occurence of processes of the target type.

label.value: decreased frequency of process from increased regulation

definition.value: The increase of regulation leads to a decreased occurence of processes of the target process type.
regulation of a process duration is a process that modulates the frequency of another process relative to some reference process.
regulation of a process duration is a process that modulates the duration of another process relative to some reference process.

label.value: increased duration of process from increased regulation

definition.value: increased duration of process from increased regulation is a process in which the duration of the target process is increased as a result of increased regulation.

label.value: decreased duration of process from increased regulation

definition.value: decreased duration of process from increased regulation is a process in which the duration of the target process is decreased as a result of increased regulation.
regulation of a process spatial extent is a process that modulates the spatial extent of another process relative to some reference process.

label.value: increased spatial extent of process from increased regulation

definition.value: The increase of regulation leads to a increased spatial extent of the target process.

label.value: decreased spatial extent of process from decreased regulation

definition.value: The increase of regulation leads to a decreased spatial extent of the target process.

label.value: maintenance of spatial extent of process

definition.value: maintenance of spatial extent of process is a regulation of a process' spatial extent within some specified parameter.
maintenance of duration of process is a process that regulates a target process to maintain its duration within an expected interval.
maintenance of frequency of process is a process that regulates the number of occurences of a target process type to a specified number or interval.
regulation of a participant quantity is the regulation of a process in which the quantity of its partcipants is changed.

label.value: increased object production from increased regulation

definition.value: increased regulation leads to an increase in the number of target objects of a specified type.

label.value: decreased object production from increased regulation

definition.value: increased regulation leads to a decrease in the number of target objects of a specified type.

label.value: increased object consumption from increased regulation

definition.value: increased regulation leads to an increase in the consumption of an object of specified type.

label.value: decreased object consumption from increased regulation

definition.value: increased regulation leads to an decrease in the consumption of an object of specified type.
A process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of process involved in the consumption of an object.
regulation of a participant quantity is the regulation of a process in which the quantity of a selected participant is increased.

label.value: maintenance of quantity of object production

definition.value: maintenance of quantity of object production is a regulation of object production in which the number of objects produced is held more or less constant.

label.value: maintenance of level of object consumption

definition.value: regulation of a participant quantity is the regulation of a process in which the quantity of a selected participant is maintained at a steady level.
number of objects produced is a count of objects that were produced in some process.
number of objects consumed is a count of objects that were consumed in some process.

label.value: difference in number of objects produced

definition.value: A difference in number of objects produced is a count of the number of objects produced with respect to a second variable (space, time, etc)

label.value: increase in number of objects produced

definition.value: An increase in the number of objects produced is the positive value of a difference in number of objects produced.

label.value: decrease in number of objects produced

definition.value: An decrease in the number of objects produced is the negative value of a difference in number of objects produced.
user account allows a user to authenticate to system services and be granted authorization to access them.
An annotation is a written explanatory or critical description, or other in-context information (e.g., pattern, motif, link), that has been associated with data or other types of information.
A comment is a verbal or written remark often related to an added piece of information, or an observation or statement.
An audio recording is an electrical or mechanical inscription and re-creation of sound waves, such as spoken voice, singing, instrumental music, or sound effects.
